                    <p><strong>Excellent!</strong> <strong>RNA polymerase</strong> is the essential enzyme that must bind to the promoter region before transcription can begin. Think of the promoter as a "Start Here" sign that RNA polymerase recognizes. Once bound, RNA polymerase will unwind the DNA double helix and start reading the template strand to create an mRNA copy!</p>
                    <p>🔍 <strong>Fun fact:</strong> In humans, there are three types of RNA polymerase, but RNA polymerase II is the one that transcribes protein-coding genes!</p>
