                <div class="description" id="description-3">
                    <h2>🧲 Perfect Base Pairing!</h2>
                    <p><strong>You've got it!</strong> RNA polymerase reads the DNA template and creates a complementary <strong>mRNA strand</strong>! Remember the key difference: RNA does not have the base Thymine - it has Uracil instead. So A pairs with U, T pairs with A, G pairs with C, and C pairs with G. It's like taking dictation with a different alphabet!</p>
                    <p>🔍 <strong>Key fact:</strong> RNA uses Uracil (U) instead of Thymine (T) because it's easier for the cell to make and RNA is temporary!</p>
                </div>
                <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 20px;">
                    <button class="nav-btn back-btn" id="back-3" onclick="previousStep()">Back</button>
