                    <div style="font-size: 4em; margin-bottom: 20px;">🧬➡️📝</div>
                    <div class="prompt">
                        Great! You've made a fresh mRNA copy. What happens to this newly made mRNA before it can be used?
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="choices">
                    <button class="choice" onclick="makeChoice(4, false, 'The mRNA isn\'t ready yet - it needs processing first!')">It immediately leaves the nucleus</button>
                    <button class="choice" onclick="makeChoice(4, true, 'Exactly! The raw mRNA must be processed before it can be used!')">It gets processed and edited</button>
                    <button class="choice" onclick="makeChoice(4, false, 'Ribosomes are in the cytoplasm, but mRNA must be processed first!')">It goes directly to ribosomes</button>
                </div>
                <div class="feedback" id="feedback-4"></div>
                <div class="description" id="description-4">
                    <h2>📝 Processing Required!</h2>
                    <p><strong>Perfect reasoning!</strong> The freshly made mRNA is like a rough draft that needs editing before it can be used. In eukaryotic cells, the raw mRNA transcript must undergo <strong>processing</strong> - removing unnecessary parts (introns) and keeping the important coding parts (exons). This ensures only the correct genetic information gets translated into protein!</p>
                    <p>🔍 <strong>Why processing matters:</strong> Without proper processing, the mRNA would contain "junk" sequences that would make a defective protein!</p>
                </div>
                <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 20px;">
                    <button class="nav-btn back-btn" id="back-4" onclick="previousStep()">Back</button>
