                        <div class="draggable" draggable="true" ondragstart="dragStart(event)" data-keep="true">Exon 1 (coding)</div>
                        <div class="draggable" draggable="true" ondragstart="dragStart(event)" data-keep="false">Intron 2 (junk)</div>
                        <div class="draggable" draggable="true" ondragstart="dragStart(event)" data-keep="true">Exon 2 (coding)</div>
                        <div class="draggable" draggable="true" ondragstart="dragStart(event)" data-keep="true">Exon 3 (coding)</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="drag-area" id="mRNA-box" ondrop="drop(event)" ondragover="allowDrop(event)" ondragleave="dragLeave(event)">
                        <div id="drop-instruction" style="color: #666;">Drag the parts to keep here!</div>
                    </div>
                    <div id="processing-feedback" style="text-align: center; margin: 10px 0; font-weight: bold;"></div>
                </div>
                <div class="feedback" id="feedback-5"></div>
                <div class="description" id="description-5">
                    <h2>✂️ Perfect RNA Processing!</h2>
                    <p><strong>Excellent editing skills!</strong> You kept only the <strong>exons</strong> (coding sequences) and removed the <strong>introns</strong> (non-coding junk)! Plus, the cell adds a <strong>5' cap</strong> (like a protective hat) and a <strong>poly-A tail</strong> (like a long scarf) to protect the mRNA during its journey!</p>
                    <p>🔍 <strong>Fun analogy:</strong> It's like editing a movie - cut out the boring scenes, keep the good parts, and add opening and closing credits!</p>
                </div>
                <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 20px;">
